meanings.definition: The ability to move or think easily, flexibly, and quickly.
examples: Being able to do an obstacle course shows great physical agility.

images.alt: Photo of a dancer in mid-air.
images.description: A dancer has lept into the air with arms extended away and above his body. His legs and feet point toward the lower left of the picture. The photo has captured the moment when the dancer is suspended in mid-air.
images.caption: Moving quickly and flexibly shows agility.

examples: The light built into my cell phone is portable, while the big lamp in my house is not.

images.alt: Photo of a person standing on portable staris.
images.description: This photo shows a set of stairs build on a frame with a wheel at each of four courners. Hand rails are on each side of five stairs. A person stands at the top of the stairs and is reaching ou toward a box. Nex to the portable stairs is a second person reaching up over their head and holding onto a box.
images.caption: Portable steps can be moved to wherever workers in this warehouse need them.

examples: The soccer player darted to the left to quickly get by the defending player.

images.alt: Photo of a small chipmunk running over grass.
images.description: A small brown animal, a chipmunk, with a small head and ears, bushy tail, and brown and white stripes on its back. The chipmunk holds a nut in its mouth. The chipmunk runs across grass. The chipmunk appears to be suspended in mid-air because the photo shows it in the middle of its stride as it runs.
images.caption: Small animals like this chipmunk dart quickly to avoid being caught.

meanings.definition: To gather in a small, close group.
examples: The team huddled together in a small circle so that the other team could not hear the plan.

images.alt: Photo of a teammates gathered close together.
images.description: Members of a team are gathered close together, leaning together toward the center of a small circle.
images.caption: Teams sometimes gather close together in a huddle to make plans.

meanings.definition: The result of an accident or destruction; a shipwreck is an example of a wreck.
examples: The driver turned the stearing wheel and pressed the brake to avoid a car wreck.

images.alt: Photo showing crushed car and broken glass.
images.description: Photo showing a car. The front of the car is bent, the hood of the car is lifted up, and the side door is open. Glass from the front windshield, side mirror, and side window are shown flying through the air.
images.caption: This car crashed into something and is now a wreck.

meanings.definition: To gather and keep for future use.
examples: Many animals collect and store food in the fall so that they will have enough to eat over the winter.

images.alt: Photo of a farm with barns and two tall silos.
images.description: Photo shows several low buildings with two round tower-like buildings rising high between them. The tall buildings are called silos. A road can be see in the foreground of the photo.
images.caption: Tall silos store wheat and other grain harvested on farms.

meanings.definition: to gather and keep for future use.
examples: Before a big storm, people are encouraged to stockpile food and medicine in case of emergency.

images.alt: Photo of a pile of sand under a tall ramp.
images.description: Photo shows a cone-shaped pile of sand beneath a ramp. The ramp extends from an area in the back of the photo, low to the ground, to high above the ground immediately above the pile of sand.
images.caption: Stockpiling sand.

examples: It is astonishing that sea turtles can for live up to 152 years.

images.alt: Photo of a woman with an astonished expression.
images.description: A man can be partially seen in the foreground of the photo. Woman stands in the background of a photo, looking around the man. Her eyes and mouth are wide open. Her head is tilted to the left.
images.caption: Woman with an astonished expression.

meanings.definition: A group of things that are the same in some way.
examples: Fruit is one type of food, meat is another type of food.

images.caption: Ducks and geese are types of water birds.

meanings.definition: A group of things that are the same in some way.
examples: Food can be put into categories like desserts, drinks, dinner foods, and more.

images.alt: Photo of ducks and geese floating on water.

meanings.definition: To advance to another state over time.
examples: Taliah outlined her ideas as she she developed her composition.
Doing an Extreme Triathlon, where you swim 5 miles, bike 225 miles, and then run 52 miles, is an amazing accomplishment!

meanings.definition: to come to possess over time.
examples: Taliah acquired the ideas for her poem by observing nature and talking with her friends.
